On USDA orders, Rochester Meats Inc., of Rochester, Minn., which supplies meat for restaurants and institutions, recalled 170,780 pounds of product last week.
The recalled products include frozen ground beef patties, ground chuck patties, chopped beefsteak, beef patties, meat for chili, beef patty mix and pure beef bulk.
The people became ill while visiting the Sunday River Ski Resort in Bethel, Maine, said Dr. Kathleen Gensheimer, state epidemiologist for the Maine Department of Human Services.
Bil Mar Foods in Zeeland, Mich., recalled 15 million pounds of hot dogs and deli meats in December because of possible contamination with listeria.
